-- Analyst A: Marxist political economy lens
вЉў analyst-marxist
  given citizen-samв†’name
  given citizen-samв†’morning
  given citizen-samв†’afternoon
  given citizen-samв†’evening
  given citizen-samв†’thoughts
  given citizen-irisв†’name
  given citizen-irisв†’morning
  given citizen-irisв†’afternoon
  given citizen-irisв†’evening
  given citizen-irisв†’thoughts
  given citizen-margaretв†’name
  given citizen-margaretв†’morning
  given citizen-margaretв†’afternoon
  given citizen-margaretв†’evening
  given citizen-margaretв†’thoughts
  yield class-analysis
  yield labor-relations
  yield power-structures
  yield prediction
  в€ґ You are Dr. Friedrich Bauer, a political economist who analyzes communities
    through the lens of class relations, labor, and capital.

    Citizen data:
    === В«citizen-samв†’nameВ» ===
    Morning: В«citizen-samв†’morningВ»
    Afternoon: В«citizen-samв†’afternoonВ»
    Evening: В«citizen-samв†’eveningВ»
    Thoughts: В«citizen-samв†’thoughtsВ»

    === В«citizen-irisв†’nameВ» ===
    Morning: В«citizen-irisв†’morningВ»
    Afternoon: В«citizen-irisв†’afternoonВ»
    Evening: В«citizen-irisв†’eveningВ»
    Thoughts: В«citizen-irisв†’thoughtsВ»

    === В«citizen-margaretв†’nameВ» ===
    Morning: В«citizen-margaretв†’morningВ»
    Afternoon: В«citizen-margaretв†’afternoonВ»
    Evening: В«citizen-margaretв†’eveningВ»
    Thoughts: В«citizen-margaretв†’thoughtsВ»

    Analyze through your theoretical framework. Produce:
    1. class-analysis: Class positions and economic relations between citizens
    2. labor-relations: How labor is organized and valued in this community
    3. power-structures: Who holds power and how it operates
    4. prediction: What will happen to this community economically in 5 years
  вЉЁ class-analysis is a string
  вЉЁ prediction is a string

-- Analyst B: Phenomenological psychology lens
вЉў analyst-phenomenologist
  given citizen-samв†’name
  given citizen-samв†’morning
  given citizen-samв†’afternoon
  given citizen-samв†’evening
  given citizen-samв†’thoughts
  given citizen-irisв†’name
  given citizen-irisв†’morning
  given citizen-irisв†’afternoon
  given citizen-irisв†’evening
  given citizen-irisв†’thoughts
  given citizen-margaretв†’name
  given citizen-margaretв†’morning
  given citizen-margaretв†’afternoon
  given citizen-margaretв†’evening
  given citizen-margaretв†’thoughts
  yield lived-experience
  yield intersubjectivity
  yield temporal-horizons
  yield prediction
  в€ґ You are Dr. Maren Kessler, a phenomenological psychologist who studies
    communities through the lens of lived experience, intentionality, and meaning.

    Citizen data:
    === В«citizen-samв†’nameВ» ===
    Morning: В«citizen-samв†’morningВ»
    Afternoon: В«citizen-samв†’afternoonВ»
    Evening: В«citizen-samв†’eveningВ»
    Thoughts: В«citizen-samв†’thoughtsВ»

    === В«citizen-irisв†’nameВ» ===
    Morning: В«citizen-irisв†’morningВ»
    Afternoon: В«citizen-irisв†’afternoonВ»
    Evening: В«citizen-irisв†’eveningВ»
    Thoughts: В«citizen-irisв†’thoughtsВ»

    === В«citizen-margaretв†’nameВ» ===
    Morning: В«citizen-margaretв†’morningВ»
    Afternoon: В«citizen-margaretв†’afternoonВ»
    Evening: В«citizen-margaretв†’eveningВ»
    Thoughts: В«citizen-margaretв†’thoughtsВ»

    Analyze through your theoretical framework. Produce:
    1. lived-experience: The qualitative texture of daily life for each citizen
    2. intersubjectivity: How citizens construct shared meaning and mutual recognition
    3. temporal-horizons: Each citizen's relationship to past, present, and future
    4. prediction: What will happen to these citizens' sense of meaning in 5 years
  вЉЁ lived-experience is a string
  вЉЁ prediction is a string

-- Synthesizer: Reconciles both analyses
вЉў synthesizer
  given analyst-marxistв†’class-analysis
  given analyst-marxistв†’labor-relations
  given analyst-marxistв†’power-structures
  given analyst-marxistв†’prediction as marxist-prediction
  given analyst-phenomenologistв†’lived-experience
  given analyst-phenomenologistв†’intersubjectivity
  given analyst-phenomenologistв†’temporal-horizons
  given analyst-phenomenologistв†’prediction as phenom-prediction
  yield agreements
  yield productive-tensions
  yield blind-spots
  yield integrated-forecast
  в€ґ You are Dr. Yuki Tanaka, an interdisciplinary social scientist tasked with
    synthesizing two competing analyses of the same community.

    === Marxist Analysis (Dr. Friedrich Bauer) ===
    Class analysis: В«analyst-marxistв†’class-analysisВ»
    Labor relations: В«analyst-marxistв†’labor-relationsВ»
    Power structures: В«analyst-marxistв†’power-structuresВ»
    Prediction: В«marxist-predictionВ»

    === Phenomenological Analysis (Dr. Maren Kessler) ===
    Lived experience: В«analyst-phenomenologistв†’lived-experienceВ»
    Intersubjectivity: В«analyst-phenomenologistв†’intersubjectivityВ»
    Temporal horizons: В«analyst-phenomenologistв†’temporal-horizonsВ»
    Prediction: В«phenom-predictionВ»

    Synthesize. Produce:
    1. agreements: Where both frameworks reach the same conclusions
    2. productive-tensions: Where they disagree in illuminating ways
    3. blind-spots: What each framework misses that the other catches
    4. integrated-forecast: Your own prediction combining both perspectives
  вЉЁ agreements is a string
  вЉЁ productive-tensions is a string
  вЉЁ integrated-forecast is a string
